Abdul Ali lang-bn  ; born 6 May 1969, best known as Ali Jacko lang-bn  , is an England English former kickboxer who held world titles in the lightweight division. He also ran JKO Productions, which was part of the kickboxing promotion of Sky Sports and Channel 5.

Early life
Ali was born in the East End of London East End of London. He is of British Bangladeshi Bangladeshi descentcite web  url=http://www.britbangla.net/successprofiles.html#jacko title=Jacko Ali work=British Bengali Success Stories publisher=BritBangla date=  accessdate=1 March 2014 and lived in Bangladesh for six years.cite web  url=http://www.alijacko.com/alijacko-biodata.html title=Bio Data publisher=CA Foundation / Ali Jacko date=  accessdate=1 March 2014 His late fathercite web  url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AbdkxGUo6hI title=Ali Jacko work=Straight Dialogue publisher=Channel i date=15 September 2013 accessdate=1 March 2014 Mohammed Chamak Ali was born in Farigow, Jawa Bazar, Chhatak Upazila Chhatak in Sylhet Division, East Pakistan now Sunamganj District Sunamganj, Bangladesh.cite web  url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VHknK34F83s title=Ali Jacko work=Straight Dialogue publisher=Channel i date=15 September 2013 accessdate=1 March 2014cite news  last=  first=  url=http://www.sylhetexpress.com/syfdiapicgel.php?SyfdianewsID=23628#newstop title=       location=Sylhet work=  publisher=Sylhet Express.com date=1 August 2013 accessdate=1 March 2014 Ali has three younger brothers and two younger sisters.cite web  url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bKjXiKaBX90 title=Jacko Ali work=Straight Dialogue publisher=Channel i date=15 September 2013 accessdate=1 March 2014

Ali attended Sir John Cass Redcoat School. At an early age, he played Junior League football and became the Freestyle BMX BMX Freestyle Schoolboy champion. From 1987, at the age of 17, he ran his own fashion design and manufacturing business.

Kickboxing career
In 1986, Ali started training as a kickboxer. On 2 December 1990, he won his first B.I.K.M.A British lightweight kickboxing title. In February 1996, he won the W.M.O European kickboxing title. On 3 October 1999, he won the W.K.N World Inter-Continental Championship. On 26 May 1996, he defeated Frederic Pierre to win the W.K.O World lightweight kickboxing title at The Island in Ilford. In June 2000, Ali took his second World lightweight kickboxing title, this time in the World Kickboxing Network belt.cite news  last=  first=  url=https://groups.google.com/d/msg/soc.culture.bangladesh/HUgJ6uQmmjE/I1x-PmzScTUJ title=Another Ali another Champion location=Dhaka work=  publisher=Dhaka Courier date=17 January 1998 accessdate=1 March 2014cite web url=http://www.cluboops.plus.com/cafs/ title=Chamak Ali Foundation UK BD publisher=Chamak Ali Foundation date=  accessdate=1 March 2014

Ali became the first Asian to win British, European, Inter-Continental and Work Full-Contact kickboxing championships. He had a 45 fight career, with one defeat by submission due to injury. Ali's manager and trainer Eddie Dujon took him through his British, European and World Championship fights. Ali retired in 2002.

Media career
In July 1997, Ali launched JKO TV, which produces and provides programmes for terrestrial, satellite and corporate clients. It filmed Thai and kickboxing on Sky Sports and Channel 5.cite web  url=http://www.muaythaionline.org/fightinfo/jko2003.html title=Results from Ali Jacko's show publisher=Muay Thai Online Club year=2003 accessdate=1 March 2014

In June 2000, Ali launched the UK's first all Kick / Thai-boxing magazine Kick Boxing UK.cite news  last=  first=  url=http://www.prokick.com/archive/archive/HTML/kbnews/kbnewsjun00.htm title=World Kickboxing News location=  work=  publisher=Prokick date=June 2000 accessdate=1 March 2014

Awards
Ali won the Canary Wharf Sporting Personality Award in 2001 and the UK Asian Sporting Award in 2003.

Personal life
Ali is a Muslim, and lives in London with his wife and son.cite web  url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d-RlYLzfKOw title=Jacko Ali work=StraightDialogue publisher=Channel i date=15 September 2013 accessdate=1 March 2014 His mother lives in Bangladesh.cite web  url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Mgq9VA2zjUQ title=Jacko Ali work=StraightDialogue publisher=Channel i date=15 September 2013 accessdate=1 March 2014

